Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addObjFPlanCutBox(25.10)                              addObjFPlanCutBox(25.10)

Name
       addObjFPlanCutBox  -  Specifies  the rectilinear shape of floorplan ob-
       jects by describing the cut out area

Syntax
        addObjFPlanCutBox

       [-help]

       type

       name

       boxlist

       Specifies the rectilinear shape of floorplan objects by describing  the
       cut out area. The floorplan objects include block top cell, module con-
       straint  (guide,  region,  fence), layershape, pin, net, group, and in-
       stance. The command creates a rectilinear cut box for an object. A rec-
       tilinear object is comprised of two or more boxes. To use this command,
       divide the required cut out area into one or more  bounding  boxes  and
       specify  the  coordinates of each bounding box in the command. Once you
       run the command, the rectilinear cut area disappears  from  the  object
       after  a  redraw.  You  can  use the command at any point in the design
       flow.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each addObjFPlanCutBox parameter. For a detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command:

              man addObjFPlanCutBox

       <name> Specifies the name of the object for type.

              Data_type: string, required

       <type> Specifies the type of object for name. This can be:

              * Cell

              * Group

              * Instance

              * Layershape

              * Module

              * Net

              * Pin

              Data_type: string, required

       <boxList>
              Specifies the rectilinear shape of an object. The  box list must
              be specified in the following format: {{x1 y1 x2 y2} ....}

              Data_type: list, required

Example
       The following example defines the rectilinear shape of the module  mod-
       ule_A by specifying 2 rectilinear cut boxes defined by coordinates (x1,
       y1), (x2, y2), (x3, y3), and (x4, y4).

       addObjFPlanCutBox Module module_A {{x1 y1 x2 y2} {x3 y3 x4 y4}}

